CALL FOR PAPERS


The 32nd Annual ACM SIGIR Conference July 19-23 2009, Boston, USA


SIGIR is the major international forum for the presentation of new =20
research results and for the demonstration of new systems and =20
techniques in the broad field of information retrieval (IR). The =20
Conference and Program Chairs invite all those working in areas =20
related to IR to submit original papers, posters, and proposals for =20
tutorials, workshops, and demonstrations of systems. SIGIR 2009 =20
welcomes contributions related to any aspect of IR theory and =20
foundation, techniques, and applications. Relevant topics include, but =20=

are not limited to:


* IR Theory and Models (e.g., all kinds of formal IR models including =20=

language models and fusion of results, user/task-based IR theory)

* IR Platforms and Scalability (e.g., IR architecture including =20
distributed/P2P, efficiency, scalability, indexing, compression)

* IR Evaluation (e.g., test collections, evaluation methods and =20
metrics, experimental design, data collection and analysis)

* Document Representation and Content Analysis (e.g., text =20
representation, document structure/discourse analysis, linguistic =20
analysis-based representation, non-topical representation)

* Query Language and Query Analysis (e.g., structured queries, query =20
representation, query intent analysis)

* User Modeling and Interactive IR (e.g., user models, user studies, =20
user interface and visualization, all kinds of feedback techniques, =20
query log analysis, personalized search)

* Machine Learning for IR (e.g., learning to rank, probabilistic topic =20=

models, all kinds of learning techniques applied to IR)

* Information Extraction and Summarization (e.g., entity/relation =20
extraction, sentiment analysis, summarization, discovery of knowledge/=20=

patterns from text)

* Categorization, Clustering, and Filtering (e.g., text =20
categorization, clustering, content-based filtering, collaborative =20
filtering)

* Multimedia IR (e.g., image IR, video IR, speech/audio IR, music IR, =20=

analysis of multimedia content)

* Question Answering and Cross-Language IR (e.g., question answering, =20=

non-English IR, cross-language IR, machine translation for IR)

* Web IR (e.g., link analysis, query log analysis, social tagging, =20
social networks, ad targeting, blog/forum IR)

* Digital Libraries and Other IR Applications (e.g., digital =20
libraries, enterprise/intranet search, distributed IR, genomics IR, =20
mobile IR, any domain-specific IR application)

* IR and Database Search (e.g., XML retrieval, structured queries, =20
ranking in databases)




IMPORTANT DATES:
Jan 19, 2009 Abstracts for full research papers due
Jan 26, 2009 Full research paper submissions due
Feb 2, 2009 Workshop proposals due
Feb 23, 2009 Posters, demonstration, and tutorial proposals due
Mar 2, 2009 Doctoral consortium proposals due
Mar 9, 2009 Notification of workshop acceptances
Apr 11, 2009 All other acceptance notification



Information on how to submit will be available by mid-December, 2008 at
http://www.sigir2009.org/


